New Records: New Zealand won their first match against Australia in Australia since December 2011.
Key Match Events: Devon Conway scored an unbeaten 92 off 58 balls.
Tim Southee took 3 wickets for 6 runs in 2.1 overs.
Mitchell Santner took 3 wickets for 31 runs in 4 overs.
New Zealand dismissed Australia for 111 in 17.1 overs.
Glenn Phillips' catch to dismiss Marcus Stoinis was a notable moment.
Pat Cummins was caught by Conway off Southee for 21 runs.
Boult took key wickets including Zampa and Starc.
Pre-Game Insights: New Zealand picked Finn Allen ahead of Martin Guptill, which paid off with Allen's explosive start.
Post-Match Reflections: Devon Conway expressed pride in the team's performance and credited Finn Allen for providing momentum.
Aaron Finch acknowledged that Australia was on the back foot from the start.
Conway mentioned the significance of the victory over Australia.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was held at the Sydney Cricket Ground.
Australia elected to field first after winning the toss.
New Zealand scored 200/3 in their 20 overs.
The match was part of the ICC Men's T20 World Cup 2022-23.
